ion brief" /></a>As part of the Integrated Management of Childhood Illnesses (IMCI), a network of US-based non-governmental organizations (NGOs) convened between 1997-2001 and through multiple meetings and workshops developed a descriptive implementation framework for household and community integrated management of childhood illnesses. Utilizing <em>three elements of action</em>, this framework is easily adaptable to the MCH Leadership Competency: Working with Communities and Systems and is an ideal tool for describing, sharing and coordinating efforts in the field.<sup>2</sup></p>    <p>View each of the <em>three elements of action</em> below and corresponding learning opportunities for: 1) <strong>Improving partnerships</strong> between health facilities and the communities they serve, 2) <strong>Increasing promotion</strong> of appropriate and accessible health care and information from community-based providers, and 3) <strong>Integrating practices</strong> focused on families critical for maternal and child health.</p><button class="accordion">1. Improving Partnerships</button>            <div class="panel">              <ul>                <li><strong><a href="http://www.phf.org/events/Pages/Webinar_Taking_Action_on_Community_Health_Improvement_Priorities.aspx">Taking Action on Community Health Improvement       Priorities</a></strong>. <em>Date Developed</em>: May 29, 2018. <em>Source</em>: Public Health Foundation. <em>Presenter(s)</em>: Jack Moran MBA, PhD;       Brett Sierra MPH; Coletta Barrett RN; Monique Marino; Shawna Mercer MSc,       PhD. <em>Type</em>: Webinar. <em>Level</em>: Introductory. <em>Length</em>: 60 minutes.<strong></strong></li>                <li><strong><a href="http://www.ca-ilg.org/webinar/improving-community-wellness-through-collaboration">Improving Community Wellness Through Collaboration</a></strong>. <em>Date Developed</em>: February 23, 2016. <em>Source</em>: Institute for Local Government. <em>Presenter(s)</em>: Richard Knecht, Christi Fee, Robb Davis. <em>Type</em>: Webinar. <em>Level</em>: Introductory. <em>Length</em>: 57 minutes.<strong></strong></li>                <li><strong><a href="https://www.all4ed.org/webinar-event/future-ready-librarians-cultivating-community-partnerships-part-of-the-future-ready-librarians-webinar-series/">Cultivating Community Partnerships</a></strong>. <em>Date Developed</em>: December 12, 2017. <em>Source</em>: Institute for Local Government. <em>Presenter(s)</em>: Richard Knecht, Christi Fee, Robb Davis. <em>Type</em>: Webinar. <em>Level</em>: Introductory. <em>Length</em>: 57 minutes.<strong></strong></li>                <li><strong><a href="https://www.insurekidsnow.gov/webinars-videos/webinars/20170620/index.html">Building Collaborative Communities: Engaging Local       Municipalities in Outreach and Enrollment Efforts</a></strong><strong>.</strong> <em>Date Developed</em>: June 20, 2017. <em>Source</em>: InsureKidsNow. <em>Presenter(s)</em>: Dawn Schluckebier. <em>Type</em>: Webinar. <em>Level</em>: Introductory. <em>Length</em>: 55 minutes.</li>              </ul>            </div>            <button class="accordion">2. Increasing Promotion</button>            <div class="panel">              <ul>                <li><strong><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bnV354YT__0">Resources on Access, Support, and Advocacy in the       Health and Insurance Worlds</a></strong>. <em>Date Developed</em>: November 26, 2013. <em>Source</em>: Genetic Alliance; Family Voices; Parent to Parent       USA. <em>Presenter(s)</em>: Rylin       Rodgers. <em>Type</em>: Webinar. <em>Level</em>: Introductory. <em>Length</em>: 56 minutes.<strong></strong></li>                <li><strong><a href="https://youtu.be/wq1Qu-sQJpI?feature=shared">Breaking Down the Rankings: Improving Access to       Health Care</a></strong>. <em>Date Developed</em>: November 14,       2013. <em>Source</em>: Robert Wood       Johnson Foundation. <em>Presenter(s)</em>:       Juli